  <h3>About</h3>
  <p><a href="http://openrlo.com">OpenRLO</a> is an open-source platform for creating Reusable Learning Objects. The source code for OpenRLO is available at <a href="https://code.google.com/p/openrlo/">Google Code Project Hosting</a>. OpenRLO was developed using the <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/net">Microsoft .NET 3.5 Framework</a>.</p>
  <p>OpenRLO uses a variety of open source software. The web UI is based on the <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/">Bootstrap</a> webapp toolkit from <a href="https://twitter.com/">Twitter</a>. This toolkit consists of a set of CSS, HTML, and Javascript components, which were modified for use by the OpenRLO website. OpenRLO also makes extensive use of <a href="http://jquery.com/">jQuery</a>, a JavaScript library for performing DOM manipulation. Finally, OpenRLO uses <a href="http://aspnetresources.com/blog/markdown_announced">Markdown.NET</a> for <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/">text-to-html conversion</a> in the RLO editing UI.</p>
  <p>OpenRLO was created by <a href="http://nathanlaan.com">Nathan Laan</a>.</p>
